# Hawkeye Sterling — Trivy vulnerability exceptions
#
# CVEs listed here are known vulnerabilities that have been evaluated and
# confirmed NOT exploitable in our deployment context. Each entry must include:
#   - CVE identifier
#   - Package affected
#   - Reason it is not exploitable here
#   - Review date and reviewer
#   - Next review date (max 12 months)
#
# Do NOT suppress CRITICAL or HIGH CVEs without MLRO/Security team sign-off.
# This file is tracked in git; any addition requires a PR review.
#
# Format: <CVE-ID>  # <package>: <justification>

# GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq  # uuid 8.3.2 (nested in exceljs 4.4.0):
# Missing buffer bounds check in uuid.v3/v4/v5/v6 when the optional `buf`
# argument is provided. The `buf` parameter is only passed by calling code
# (never from user input) and in Node.js a too-small Buffer throws a RangeError
# rather than causing memory corruption. exceljs uses uuid internally for
# spreadsheet cell identity — the `buf` argument is never used. Fix requires
# exceljs@3.4.0 downgrade (semver major — breaks XLSX streaming API).
# Review date: 2026-05-28 | Reviewer: Security team | Next review: 2027-05-28
GHSA-w5hq-g745-h8pq

# GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93  # postcss (nested in next.js 16.x):
# PostCSS XSS via unescaped </style> in CSS stringify output. Affects
# next.js 9.3.4-canary.0 through 16.3.0-canary.5 due to a bundled postcss
# < 8.5.10. postcss is a build-time CSS processor — it is never exposed at
# runtime in Netlify serverless or Docker standalone deployments; CSS is
# compiled out of the request path. No stable Next.js 16.x fix available yet.
# Review date: 2026-05-28 | Reviewer: Security team | Next review: 2027-05-28
GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93

# Note: when upstream fixes land for the above, remove these entries and
# tighten the Trivy CI step to --ignore-unfixed=false with no exceptions.
